@startuml architecture
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam packageBackgroundColor #fafafa
skinparam componentBackgroundColor #ffffff
skinparam ArrowColor #555555

title AgentAid — System Architecture

package "Agent + SDK Layer" #f4f8ff {
  [Reference Agent\n(Pydantic AI)] as Agent
  [Bare Anthropic\nSDK Example] as Bare
  component "agentaid-py SDK" as PySdk
  component "agentaid-ts SDK" as TsSdk
  database "Mock arXiv\n(default)" as Mock
  database "Real arXiv API\n(feature flag)" as Real
}

package "Server Layer (FastAPI + SQLModel)" #fff5e8 {
  [Ingest\n/ingest] as Ingest
  database "SQLite" as DB
  [Eval Orchestrator\nMode 1 + 3] as EvalOrch
  [Regression Driver\nMode 2] as RegOrch
  [Drift Workers\nADWIN · MMD · PSI] as Drift
  [REST API\n/runs · /evals · /drift\n/datasets · /regressions\n/compare] as Api
}

package "Frontend (Vite + React + TS)" #f3fff3 {
  [Drift Home  /] as Home
  [Trace Detail  /runs/:id] as Trace
  [Run Comparison  /compare] as Compare
  [Drift Detail × 3\n/drift/:signal] as DriftPage
  [Eval Results  /evals] as Evals
  [Datasets · Run List] as Other
}

Agent --> Mock : default
Agent ..> Real : if AGENTAID_USE_REAL_ARXIV
Agent --> PySdk : emit otel/genai spans
Bare --> PySdk : manual otel/genai

PySdk --> Ingest : HTTP POST\n{spans:[…]}
TsSdk --> Ingest : HTTP POST\n{spans:[…]}

Ingest --> DB : write spans + run
Ingest ..> EvalOrch : background tasks\nper terminated run
EvalOrch --> DB : write EvalResult
RegOrch --> Agent : drive dataset rows
RegOrch --> DB : write RegressionRun
Drift --> DB : poll evals + spans\n(5 s tick)
Drift --> DB : write DriftStateRow

Api <-- DB

Home --> Api : GET /drift\n GET /runs
Trace --> Api : GET /runs/:id
Compare --> Api : GET /compare
DriftPage --> Api : GET /drift/series/:signal
Evals --> Api : GET /evals/recent
Other --> Api : /datasets · /regressions

note right of PySdk
  All spans use the OpenTelemetry
  GenAI semantic conventions
  (gen_ai.* + agentaid.* attributes).
  This is the seam that makes
  AgentAid framework-agnostic.
end note

@enduml
